steps.instruction:
1. Preheat the oven to 375F
2. Lightly grease two baking sheets, or line with parchment
3. Beat together the butter, sugars, cocoa powder, salt, baking soda, baking powder, and vanilla until well blended
4. Add the egg, beating until smooth
5. Scrape the sides of the bowl, and beat again until smooth
6. If you're going to add chips, nuts, or dried fruit, beat in the 2 tablespoons milk; if you're going to bake plain cookies without add-ins, omit the milk
7. Add the flour and espresso powder, mixing to combine
8. Stir in the chips, nuts, etc., if you're using them
9. Drop the cookies by the traditional "tablespoonful" (actually about 4 measuring teaspoons) onto the prepared baking sheets, spacing them about 2" apart. A tablespoon cookie scoop works well here
10. Bake the cookies for 12 to 14 minutes, until they've lost their shiny appearance and look like they're set
11. Remove them from the oven, and cool right on the pans; or transfer to a rack to cool

#### Tips
- For smaller (2 1/2") cookies, drop the dough by the heaping teaspoonful onto the baking sheet. Bake the cookies for 9 to 10 minutes, until they appear set. Yield: about 4 dozen cookies.

ingredients.note: OPTIONAL if you add 2 cup chips/nuts/fruit
